token_lists.title: Media Memory Collection by Kika Nicolela
token_lists.description:
In the project ‘Media Memory Collection’, I collected donations of old homemade films from families in the countryside of São Paulo - the region where I was born. During an art residency at LIFT (Toronto), I digitized about 30 hours of this material, including some films in extremely bad condition. Those were scanned frame by frame in high resolution, and the frames were re-animated to become videos. Now the project goes full circle with the creation of these NFT. 

This collection I am making available has no filter, no effects - just the effects of the film’s decay, frozen at the moment of scanning. At times we can barely recognize the original image, which leaves a fertile space for fabulating new possible stories and projecting our own fiction.

The project as a whole offers a reflection about time – condensing and uniting elements such as memory, the moment and context of the recording, the documentation of time passage in the lives of the subjects and the impression of time over the media itself.

token_lists.title: Second Guesses
token_lists.description: Part of my collection on Foundation titled "One Takes" (https://foundation.app/collection/onetakes) is a series I'm going to be minting on Tezos, titled "Second Guesses". This series are those that didn't make it to "One Takes" but still evoke the same emotion and meaning in the imagery that I capture. The meaning is the same, the emotion and intention of exploration is the same. The chain is different. I'm not sure how many of these I'll produce, but I hope you enjoy the journey.

token_lists.title: ABSTRASCII B&W
token_lists.description: I developed the black and white ABSTRASCII spin-off under the influence of the abstract painting by Franz Kline that I discovered on Kerouac's "On the Road" book cover. Descriptions, though are full-blown cyberpunk with a pinch of cultural references.
